# Showcase assets

The README references these three static screenshots. Capture them from the running
app (https://rei.ttwdev.com) and drop them in this folder with these EXACT names:

- hero.png    — headline shot: a chat where you asked a roster question and Rei replied
                with an analyst-style answer that includes an inline stat table.
                The single most representative screen (sits at the top of the README).
- roster.png  — the Roster / leagues page showing a league roster with the stat columns
                (Basic / Advanced / Statcast percentile, batters + pitchers).
- chat.png    — a chat session showing the multi-session sidebar (a few past
                conversations) + a conversation, to convey the chat UX / history.

Keep them as plain PNG blobs (NOT Git LFS) — public-repo LFS bandwidth is tiny and would
break the images. Compress/optimize before committing. No GIF for now.
